The man was arrested in Rondebosch at the weekend on suspicion of trying to sell a stolen cellphone. CAPE TOWN - The Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid) is investigating the death of a man at Rondebosch police station.The man was arrested in the area on suspicion of trying to sell a stolen cellphone at the weekend.Ipid's Moses Dlamini says: The police were allegedly called and then they chained the man. When they took him out at the police station he had allegedly passed away. Ipid is investigating a death in police custody. Dlamini adds the cause of death is unknown and will form part of the investigation.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)